-- Singapore's Goodpack confirms takeover discussions with KKR
-- 
-- Tue May 20, 2014 06:00AM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, May 20 (Reuters) - Singapore's Goodpack Ltd <GPAK.SI> confirmed on Tuesday it is in discussions with KKR & Co <KKR.N> about a possible buyout by the U.S. private equity firm, the company said in a statement. [ID:nSNZ9Rn1X4]

The announcement follows reports on Monday that KKR was nearing the deal. [ID:nSNZ43FdHZ] If successful, the purchase of Goodpack would be KKR's first purchase of a listed company from its latest Asia fund, which raised $6 billion.